id: feedback/codex-t4o-parser
title: "codex t4o feedback parser"
kind: parser-contract
status: v0-seed
updated: 2026-07-01

purpose: >
  Define how Codex/T4O should parse feedback into structured database fields and
  place it in the correct bucket.

input:
  - email metadata
  - raw feedback body
  - optional linked repo path
  - optional user consent flag

output:
  feedback_id: ""
  summary: ""
  sentiment: "confused | interested | blocked | excited | concerned | neutral"
  category: "onboarding | template | ontology | feedback-form | safety | docs | agent | database | other"
  affected_node: ""
  suggested_next_move: ""
  severity: "low | medium | high"
  follow_up_allowed: "yes | no | unknown"
  database_table: "feedback_items"

placement_rule: >
  Put onboarding confusion near start/readme nodes, ontology confusion near core
  or interface nodes, safety concerns near proof/boundary, and tooling requests
  near feedback, records, database, or agents.

boundary: >
  The parser summarizes and classifies. It does not decide product truth, expose
  personal details, or overwrite canonical files without human review.

proof:
  source:
    - feedback/email-intake.yawn
    - database/feedback-intake.yawn
  status: seed-backed
